The paper deals with graph drawing and routing algorithms, which are typically studied in computer science subfields such as computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of hyperbolic geometry in the algorithm also suggests a potential connection to theoretical computer science (cs.TH). However, since the focus of the paper is on practical applications such as sensor networks, we consider cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SI, and cs.DM to be the most likely sub-categories.
